text: Once again I dont share the view that there is loads of cash on the sidelines (relative to history) - as just expressed by my pal @fundstrat on @cnbc. As I wrote yesterday on @realmoney Dec 09, 2019 | 11:15 AM EST DOUG KASS The Investing Public Is Overweight Equities

* Stocks are "over owned" and loved by individuals Investors are not bailing on stocks, mutual funds and ETFs, as suggested in a front story article in the Wall Street Journal! I couldn't disagree more with the WSJ's article which implies (as a seemingly classical contrarian

indicator) that this is bullish for stocks. The reality is that the percentage of stocks/household total assets is basically at or near an all-time high. The redemptions are essentially a rebalancing - given the ramp in equities in 2019.

Moreover, household wealth as a percentage of disposable income is back to 2000 and 2007 nosebleed levels. @SquawkCNBC @cnbcfastmoney @tomkeene @jimcramer @Sarge986 @carlquintanilla @davidfaber @michaelsantoli
